OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 31 Mar to Thu 9 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure to the southwest of the
OL,7,FUK, with weather fronts rounding the
OL,8,Fhigh to affect northern parts at
OL,9,Ftimes, is likely the dominant patter
OL,10,Fthrough this period. Wetter and
OL,11,Fwindier weather can be expected in the
OL,12,Fnorth, while further south, drier and
OL,13,Fmore settled conditions are more
OL,14,Flikely. There is a chance of deeper
OL,15,Flows moving across the UK at times,
OL,16,Fbringing wetter and windier weather
OL,17,Fmore widely. Later in the period, high
OL,18,Fpressure may spread across much of the
OL,19,FUK leading to more widespread settled
OL,20,Fconditions. Whilst temperatures will
OL,21,Fbe generally near to or a little above
OL,22,Faverage, some colder interludes are
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fpossible, especially in the north,
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fwhere there could be some wintry
OL,25,Fshowers at times.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1774534302
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 9 Apr to Thu 23 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure will likely be dominant
OL,7,Fat the start of this period. As such,
OL,8,Fplenty of dry weather seems most
OL,9,Flikely, but with changes in wind
OL,10,Fdirection leading to some quite marked
OL,11,Fdifferences in cloud amounts and
OL,12,Ftemperature from day to day. Moving
OL,13,Ffurther into April, there is a chance
OL,14,Fthat high pressure will become less
OL,15,Fdominant and thus there is a greater
OL,16,Fchance of more places seeing some rain
OL,17,Fand possible stronger winds from time
OL,18,Fto time. Overall, temperatures will
OL,19,Flikely be near to average.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
